                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                                        <placeName>Montreal</placeName>\n                                        <date>June 29, 5608</date>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>\n                                        <addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">\n                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">My dear Friend</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(4)\">I can very readily excuse<lb/> you for what I\n                                        began to think was a little piece<lb/> of neglect on your\n                                        part in delaying to write me a long<lb/> note that I know\n                                        what was the cause one which I<lb/> regalled much to hear,!\n                                                  <add>Hebrew</add> you are not to <add>?</add><lb/>\n                                        yourself for a <add>Hebrew</add> It is true that in no\n                                        period<lb/> of their existence nationally, did our brethren\n                                        stand in greater<lb/> need of instruction and of being\n                                        aroused to a due sense of their<lb/> duty than now, and\n                                        therefore, I still continue to say <add>Hebrew</add><lb/>\n                                        but do not let your health suffer by so doing, why not\n                                        take<lb/> a little recreation? Why not take a trip into\n                                                  <placeName>Montreal</placeName> this summer?<lb/>\n                                        Do you wait for a formal invitation? Here is one for you\n                                        there<lb/> “The <persName>Rev Abraham deSola</persName> sees\n                                        also many other friends will be most<lb/> happy to see the\n                                                  <persName>Rev Isaac Leeser</persName> in\n                                                  <placeName>Montreal</placeName> during the\n                                        present<lb/> summer, when, should the <persName>Rev. I\n                                                  L.</persName> determine upon coming, they<lb/>\n                                        will <sic>will</sic> endeavor to make the arrangements\n                                        which<lb/> will enable him to pass his time as pleasurably\n                                        as it is possible<lb/> to do in so outlandish a place ”\n                                        Please excuse the pink edged<lb/> not paper, but seriously,\n                                        dear Friend, I think that a trip to<lb/>\n                                        <placeName>Canada</placeName> would do you much good, and I\n                                        shall be delighted to see<lb/> you, to find you a room, to\n                                        show you my books, and (probably)<lb/> to grovel with you\n                                        over their contents.</p>\n                              <p>Receive my best thanks for your kindness in inserting the long<lb/>\n                                        notice of my lecture, I have not the least doubt as to the\n                                        party<lb/> who sent it, He <hi rend=\"underline\">is</hi> an\n                                        esteemed friend of mine, and one I believe<lb/> with whom\n                                        you are also well acquainted but as you don't<lb/> mention\n                                        names I shall not.</p>\n                              <p>You misunderstand me as regards the <add>Hebrew</add>. My object\n                                        was<lb/> to publish it in the same way as\n                                                  <persName>English's</persName> book was\n                                        republished<lb/> in <placeName>Jamaica</placeName> It would\n                                        have been an anonymous publication—<lb/> this I think I\n                                        neglected to tell you, as I write in haste, My<lb/> object\n                                        was further, to <add>?</add> from you as the person\n                                        most<lb/> able to inform me, whether there were reading\n                                        Israelites enough<lb/> in <placeName>America</placeName> to\n                                        pay for the printing of the book, not to<lb/> make it a\n                                        course of profit, that of course I would not expect.<lb/> I\n                                        know as well as you (excuse nay indulgence) that\n                                        neither<lb/> pudding nor fame was to be derived from it, but\n                                        such</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3np1x156/canvas/p1"
                }
