                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>is my estimation of the work, that I think it would do<lb/> a great\n                                        deal of good, were it generally known. I did not at all<lb/>\n                                        expect, my dear Friend, that you would gather\n                                        subscriptions<lb/> To repeat your own words “That figure is\n                                        out of the question.”<lb/> I only <add>?</add> open for what\n                                        you have readily given me<lb/> your advise, and\n                                        co-operation. Many thanks for your<lb/>\n                                        <add>?</add> as to fishing in troubled waters. I am well\n                                        convinced<lb/> I can assure you of the value &amp; truth of\n                                        what you say, but in<lb/> case of being attacked by some of\n                                        our christian friends (which I<lb/> think would be unlikely,\n                                        the publication being anonymous<lb/> I would always be in\n                                        possession of the <add>?</add> provide) by some<lb/>\n                                        <add>?</add> of controversial writers on our side the\n                                        auction so that<lb/> at all events I should have the means\n                                        if not the capability to<lb/> give them drubbing for\n                                        drubbing. I have no wish however as<lb/> I know my own\n                                        (insufficiency, to enter into controversial<lb/>\n                                        disputation, and if I desired to give to the public some of\n                                        my<lb/> translations <hi rend=\"underline\">as my own</hi> and\n                                        which I have by me I<lb/> certainly would not choose the\n                                                  <add>Hebrew</add> but rather my <hi\n                                                  rend=\"underline\">humble</hi><lb/> renderings of\n                                        our <hi rend=\"underline\">Rabbinical</hi> writers, I am more\n                                        attached to them<lb/> than to Lituanian<add>?</add>\n                                                  Caraibes<add>?</add> and always was so. Tell me,\n                                        how<lb/> would you like to receive some of these\n                                        translations for<lb/> publication in the Occident, and then,\n                                        before the matter is distributed<lb/> print off\n                                                  <sic>seperately</sic>, say 500 copies of them I\n                                        paying the difference<lb/> and receiving the books or you\n                                                  <sic>takeing</sic> those with me in the\n                                        profits<lb/> and leaving the proportionate expense. The\n                                        difference could not<lb/> be very great as there would be\n                                        but little alteration to be<lb/> made in the matter before\n                                        it is distributed and merely<lb/> the expense of paper &amp;\n                                        press work. I am sure I could dispose<lb/> of many in\n                                                  <placeName>England</placeName>\n                                        <add>?</add>. I have promised to<lb/> contribute to the\n                                        Occident and I don't know why one should<lb/> not derive\n                                        mutual benefit from the course first proposed—</p>\n                              <p>Please understand me, I do not mean that the <add>Hebrew</add>\n                                        should<lb/> so appear, but smaller works such as the\n                                                  <add>Hebrew</add><lb/>\n                                        <add>Hebrew</add> translations of<lb/> which I have made\n                                        although not completed. <sic>Dont</sic> think<lb/> either\n                                        that it is a mania for printing which leads me<lb/> to\n                                        propose this but receive it as a casual thought the<lb/>\n                                        value and practicability of which you are yourself to<lb/>\n                                        determine in your next communication. But let me</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3np1x156/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
