                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3np1x156/manifest/annotation/p4",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>before writing again By the way, your letter is dated<lb/>\n                                        <date>1<hi rend=\"sup\">st</hi> June</date> and I did not\n                                        receive it till the <date>27<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi></date>\n                                        with<lb/> the Occidents. Stand when you write, write\n                                        fully.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Now dear friend farewell for the present<lb/> with\n                                        earnest prayers for your perfect health and<lb/> general\n                                        welfare believe me</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(4)\">Very truly yours</p>\n                              <p>\n                                        <placeName>\n                                                  <sic>1 Pres deVille Plase</sic>\n                                        </placeName>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(5)\">\n                                        <persName role=\"author\">Abraham deSola</persName>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>A lady (<persName>Miss Miriam Belisario</persName>) formerly a\n                                        pupil<lb/> of mine has lately published a Hebrew &amp;\n                                        English <add>?</add><lb/> advertised in the day to Jewish\n                                        papers as <add>Hebrew</add> &amp; he<lb/>she wishes that she\n                                        has sent me a copy, but<lb/> having entrusted it to some\n                                        person to <add>?</add> me, who<lb/> was going out to\n                                                  <placeName>Canada</placeName> I have not yet seen\n                                        it.<lb/> I would otherwise have written a review (for the\n                                        sake of<lb/> old acquaintanceship) for the Occident. If you\n                                        feel<lb/> disposed to resign the post of honor, or\n                                                  <sic>dont</sic> intend<lb/> writing one, pray send\n                                        me the books per first<lb/> opportunity and I will endeavor\n                                        to do the<lb/> needful.</p>\n                              <div>\n                                        <p>\n                                                  <ref target=\"Occident_PDFs/Occ_6_3.pdf\">The above\n                                                  text refers to Occident Volume 6 No. 3 pages 143\n                                                  through 148. Click here to view.</ref>\n                                        </p>\n                              </div>\n                    </body>\n          </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3np1x156/canvas/p4"
                }
